Goodell said that when the group was formed about a year ago, We sent an invitation to Lucille Ball to be a member, and she sent back a check for $500 for a life membership. Miss Ball was to have received an honorary degree from the college at the homecoming scheduled for May 20. Although the comedian hadn't visited Jamestown since 1956 and had no family there, she regularly donated money to charities, civic events and Jamestown Community College, said Mayor Steven Carlson. As a model, she caught Hollywood's eye and in 1933, she was off to Hollywood. 